These past few years, I've slowly been getting more and more into woodworking as
a hobby. I decided this year that it was time to challenge myself and
make a more serious piece of furniture than I had before and set off to build a
mid-century modern style credenza.

I spent several months on this project, learning, designing, planning, and
building. I knew it would push me way out of my comfort zone and would require
a lot of firsts for me. I went to a lumber yard and worked with hardwood
(walnut) for the first time. I bought and learned how to use new tools. I spent
countless hours on YouTube learning about woodworking. I learned fun new words,
like dado and rabbet. I had the time of my life. I was miserable. I'm still not
sure which it is. One thing I'm sure of though is that I'm proud of what I
accomplished, and the feeling of having created something makes it worth it to
me.

